   "built" -> "{2026, 4, 12, 17, 58, 55.658604}", 
    "history" -> {"14.3", "", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {
     "fermionic quantum computation", "fermionic Gaussian state"}, 
    "specialkeywords" -> {}, "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True,
     "label" -> "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "WickMutualInformation[grn, {k1, k2, ...}] returns the mutual information \
between the subsystem consisting of fermion modes {k1, k2, ...}\\[Subset]{1, \
2, ..., n} and the rest in the fermionic Gaussian state (without pairing \
correlation) characterized by n*n matrix grn of single-particle Green's \
functions. WickMutualInformation[ws,{k1,k2,...}] is equivalent to \
WickMutualInformation[WickGreen[state] ,{k1,k2,...}] for Wick state ws. \
